Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:04.240
Detective Recapped here. Today, I'm going&nbsp;
to explain a Crime-Mystery film called:&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:04.240 --> 00:00:08.480
"Wild Things.” Filled to the brim with deception&nbsp;
and betrayal, this film proves that people&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:12.480
don't always turn out to be who they say they&nbsp;
are. Spoilers ahead! Watch out and take care.

00:00:13.200 --> 00:00:16.560
For the charming guidance counselor, Sam&nbsp;
Lombardo, carnal abuse is something the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:16.560 --> 00:00:19.920
seniors of Blue Bay High School should&nbsp;
know about. To educate the students,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:19.920 --> 00:00:23.920
Sam invites Detectives Ray Duquette and Gloria&nbsp;
Perez to give a lecture about the matter.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:23.920 --> 00:00:27.680
As Ray introduces himself and his partner,&nbsp;
one of the students, Suzie Toller,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:27.680 --> 00:00:32.000
shows hostility toward him and rudely walks out&nbsp;
of the auditorium. After the lecture, Sam and the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.800
detectives see Suzie immediately walk away as soon&nbsp;
she spots them. Ray informs Gloria that he busted&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:36.800 --> 00:00:41.120
Suzie the previous year for possession, while&nbsp;
Sam adds that she spent six months in Camp Nine.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:44.960
Although Suzie's reaction is understandable,&nbsp;
it's a wonder why she's too nasty towards Ray,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:44.960 --> 00:00:48.880
considering the fact that she's the one in the&nbsp;
wrong. Suzie must've felt that she was wrongfully&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:48.880 --> 00:00:53.360
jailed, or maybe, there's more to the story of her&nbsp;
arrest than the detective lets on. At the school&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:53.360 --> 00:00:57.040
entrance, Sam thanks the detectives for coming&nbsp;
to their school, and as they get to their car,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:57.040 --> 00:01:01.840
Gloria notes how Ray doesn't seem to like Sam.&nbsp;
Ray implies that Sam has a thing for school girls,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:01.840 --> 00:01:06.000
and Gloria teases him that she won’t mind sleeping&nbsp;
with the guidance counselor. Before the lecture,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:09.840
most of the girl students aren't embarrassed to&nbsp;
show their interest in Sam. It is clear enough&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:09.840 --> 00:01:14.000
that Sam is popular among them, which explains&nbsp;
Ray's coldness towards him. It's not that Ray&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:18.160
is jealous, but he thinks Sam is a womanizer who&nbsp;
would even prey on his students—a possible threat.

00:01:18.880 --> 00:01:22.480
One day, Kelly Van Ryan approaches Sam&nbsp;
after he's gone sailing with his student,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:22.480 --> 00:01:27.120
Jimmy. Obviously flirting, Kelly asks the guidance&nbsp;
counselor if she and her friend can wash his Jeep&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:27.120 --> 00:01:31.920
for the senior car wash, and Sam says they can.&nbsp;
She then asks Sam if he can give her a ride home,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:31.920 --> 00:01:35.200
saying her mother was supposed to&nbsp;
pick her up but didn't show up. Here,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:35.200 --> 00:01:39.600
Kelly shows that she isn't afraid to go after what&nbsp;
she wants, which is Sam. She doesn't even mind&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:39.600 --> 00:01:42.880
teasing him in front of another student, proving&nbsp;
that she pays no mind to what others think.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:43.440 --> 00:01:48.080
Sam seems reluctant to do it, so he offers Jimmy&nbsp;
a ride, too. They then see Suzie trying to fix&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:48.080 --> 00:01:51.680
her car on their way out of the campus, and&nbsp;
Sam asks if she needs a lift home. However,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:51.680 --> 00:01:56.000
Kelly pisses Suzie off by insulting the way she's&nbsp;
dressed, and once her car is fixed, Suzie flips&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:01.360
them off. With Kelly getting dropped off, her mom,&nbsp;
Sandra, comes out of the balcony wearing a bikini.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:01.360 --> 00:02:05.360
To Kelly's irritation, Sandra asks Sam if he'd&nbsp;
like to have a drink with her inside, but Sam&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:09.520
politely refuses and quickly drives away. Sandra's&nbsp;
way of talking to Sam indicates they used to be&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:13.600
romantically involved, and Kelly doesn't even&nbsp;
bother hiding her annoyance. She's probably irate&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:17.200
that she has to compete with her mother for Sam's&nbsp;
attention, but Sam isn't even interested in them.

00:02:17.920 --> 00:02:22.560
On Sunday, Kelly gets to washing Sam’s jeep. She&nbsp;
then enters the house without Sam's permission,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:22.560 --> 00:02:26.400
and as she stands there and drips water on&nbsp;
the floor, she looks at Sam salaciously.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:30.400
Later on, Kelly comes out of the house looking&nbsp;
upset with her hair and clothes disheveled.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:33.600
When Kelly comes out of the house, it's hard&nbsp;
to determine if something really happened to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:33.600 --> 00:02:37.680
her because there's no proof or witness. Her&nbsp;
earlier behavior, her dishevelled appearance,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:37.680 --> 00:02:40.400
and the upset look on her face are&nbsp;
telling completely different things.

00:02:40.400 --> 00:02:44.560
The next day, as Sandra spends the day in bed&nbsp;
with Frankie, she receives a call from Kelly's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:44.560 --> 00:02:48.480
school informing her that her daughter was absent.&nbsp;
She quickly asks Sam if he's heard from Kelly,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:48.480 --> 00:02:53.280
but Sam doesn't know where she is. As they talk,&nbsp;
Sandra hears her daughter outside, skeet-shooting,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:53.280 --> 00:02:57.040
so she tells Sam she's already found her. She then&nbsp;
tells him that it was nice seeing him the other&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:57.040 --> 00:03:01.200
day, but Sam isn't in the mood for her games and&nbsp;
just ends the call. When Sandra asks her daughter&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:05.680
why she skipped school, Kelly starts crying and&nbsp;
says she misses her dad. Though Sandra sympathizes&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:05.680 --> 00:03:09.200
with her daughter, all she could tell her is that&nbsp;
she isn’t sure why her father killed himself.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:09.760 --> 00:03:13.920
As Kelly continues to cry, she confesses&nbsp;
that Sam Lombardo violated her. Of course,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:13.920 --> 00:03:17.680
it’s only natural that Sandra will quickly&nbsp;
believe anything Kelly says. Though they don’t&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:17.680 --> 00:03:21.680
always see things eye-to-eye, Sandra is still&nbsp;
a mother who is protective of her daughter.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:21.680 --> 00:03:25.120
But things aren’t quite adding up, and if only&nbsp;
Sandra had spent more time with her daughter&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:25.120 --> 00:03:28.720
and less time with her lover, then maybe she&nbsp;
would see right away if Kelly’s lying or not.

00:03:28.720 --> 00:03:33.200
Wasting no time, Sandra contacts Ray and Gloria,&nbsp;
informing them of what happened to her daughter.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:33.200 --> 00:03:37.680
As Gloria records her statement, Kelly starts&nbsp;
recounting the events at Sam's house. According&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:37.680 --> 00:03:41.680
to her, Sam started rubbing her shoulders,&nbsp;
and she let him because he was a nice guy.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:46.240
The next thing she knew, Sam's hand was already&nbsp;
in her shorts from behind. Despite her protests,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:46.240 --> 00:03:50.560
Sam had her hands pinned behind her and repeatedly&nbsp;
urged her to just let it happen. When Sam suddenly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:50.560 --> 00:03:54.640
stopped, he insulted her by saying no little&nbsp;
girl could ever make him finish. Once Ray,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:54.640 --> 00:03:59.040
Gloria, and Bryce Hunter are done watching Kelly's&nbsp;
recorded confession, Gloria deduces that nothing&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:59.040 --> 00:04:03.280
happened between Sam and Kelly. Gloria believes&nbsp;
Kelly was just acting because she was disappointed&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:03.280 --> 00:04:07.280
that Sam didn't come on to her when she wanted&nbsp;
him to. Gloria then suggests they make Kelly take&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:07.280 --> 00:04:12.480
a polygraph test, but Ray opposes, saying that her&nbsp;
lawyer, Tom Baxter, will cut her down. Gloria gets&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:12.480 --> 00:04:16.560
mad that Ray won't back her up, and as they argue,&nbsp;
Bryce tells them to start with the investigation.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:16.560 --> 00:04:21.120
It's difficult to explain how Gloria immediately&nbsp;
concluded that Kelly was lying. It may come from&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:21.120 --> 00:04:24.880
her experience as a detective to quickly tell&nbsp;
if a person is telling the truth or not. But&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:24.880 --> 00:04:29.440
since they lack any physical evidence, Gloria is&nbsp;
right to call for a lie detector test for Kelly.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:32.880
However, they live in a place where even the&nbsp;
authorities are afraid of powerful and wealthy&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:32.880 --> 00:04:37.440
people like Sandra Van Ryan and Tom Baxter.&nbsp;
Unfortunately for them, Kelly is a Van Ryan.

00:04:38.160 --> 00:04:41.760
After learning about Kelly's accusations and&nbsp;
that Sandra is pushing for his suspension,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:45.600
Sam gets mad and asks Artie why the board would&nbsp;
decide without hearing his side first. Feeling&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:50.080
sorry for him, Artie tells him to just wait until&nbsp;
his name is cleared, but Sam won't hear him out.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:50.080 --> 00:04:53.760
Sam believes that no one ever gets cleared from an&nbsp;
accusation like that, adding that it will follow&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:53.760 --> 00:04:57.760
him wherever he goes. Artie then advises him to&nbsp;
hire a lawyer, but he isn't sure where to find one&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:57.760 --> 00:05:01.840
who would agree to go up against the Van Ryans in&nbsp;
court. Another proof that money can buy anything,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:01.840 --> 00:05:06.080
Sandra uses her influence to convince the board&nbsp;
to suspend Sam without going through due process.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:06.080 --> 00:05:09.120
Artie, who has a position in school,&nbsp;
can't even do anything about it,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:09.120 --> 00:05:12.240
which is even more upsetting because he&nbsp;
knows what they're doing to Sam isn't fair.

00:05:12.240 --> 00:05:16.720
After some time, Sam hires Ken Bowden to defend&nbsp;
him against the Van Ryans. When Sam insists that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:16.720 --> 00:05:20.400
he's just Kelly’s guidance counselor and nothing&nbsp;
more, Bowden assures him he's got nothing to worry&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:20.400 --> 00:05:24.240
about. Even though most people are afraid to&nbsp;
go up against someone more powerful than them,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:24.240 --> 00:05:28.240
there are still few who are willing to do what's&nbsp;
right, and one of them is Ken Bowden. Bowden isn't&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:28.240 --> 00:05:31.840
scared to face the Van Ryans in court, but&nbsp;
instead, he considers it to be a challenge.

00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:36.640
That night, Sam goes to a local bar to&nbsp;
drink before going home. As he drives,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:36.640 --> 00:05:40.880
he notices a vehicle following him. It bumps&nbsp;
into his Jeep until he goes over the swamp.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:40.880 --> 00:05:44.720
Bleeding, Sam manages to get out of his Jeep.&nbsp;
But the driver, who turns out to be Frankie,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:44.720 --> 00:05:48.800
punches him and starts beating him up. The next&nbsp;
day, Bowden goes to Sam's house and gets startled&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:48.800 --> 00:05:53.040
when Sam comes out with a gun pointed at him.&nbsp;
Sam quickly apologizes and invites Bowden inside&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:53.040 --> 00:05:57.360
the house, where he informs him that Frankie Condo&nbsp;
attacked him and was driving Sandra's Range Rover.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:57.360 --> 00:06:00.640
Bowden wants him to go to the cops&nbsp;
and make a statement, but Sam refuses,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:00.640 --> 00:06:04.160
saying he doesn't need any more trouble from&nbsp;
Sandra. Confident that they'll win against the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:04.160 --> 00:06:08.000
Van Ryans, Bowden brings up the time when Kelly&nbsp;
ran away from home and stayed in a motel to get&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.160
high after her father killed himself. Bowden then&nbsp;
says the authorities haven't taken his statement&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:12.160 --> 00:06:15.440
yet because they're still looking for dirt,&nbsp;
which they won't find. When Bowden looks at&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:15.440 --> 00:06:18.800
Sam and asks for confirmation, Sam simply&nbsp;
says he doesn't sleep with his students.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:19.360 --> 00:06:23.120
Once again, Sam's beating proves that&nbsp;
Sandra can do whatever she wants with him.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:23.120 --> 00:06:26.800
She can even have Sam killed if she wants to,&nbsp;
but of course, she'd rather see her daughter's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:26.800 --> 00:06:31.200
violator suffer first. And while Sam’s punishment&nbsp;
is already preceding the verdict, Bowden isn’t&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:31.200 --> 00:06:34.400
averse to playing dirty himself, which is&nbsp;
clear when he mentioned Kelly’s breakdown.

00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:40.320
One day, Ray and Gloria visit Suzie and her&nbsp;
grandmother, Ruby, since Suzie called them. After&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:40.320 --> 00:06:44.320
finding out that Sam isn’t arrested yet, Suzie&nbsp;
admits that Sam forced himself on her about a year&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:44.320 --> 00:06:48.960
ago in her trailer. As the detectives question&nbsp;
her, Suzie starts getting upset and aggressive,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:48.960 --> 00:06:52.480
but she still manages to tell them that once&nbsp;
Sam stopped, he said that no little girl could&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:52.480 --> 00:06:56.960
make him finish. With her statement matching&nbsp;
Kelly’s, Sam is immediately arrested. Though&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:56.960 --> 00:07:01.200
Sam vehemently insists that he’s innocent, Bowden&nbsp;
only tells him that he’s preaching to the choir.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:01.200 --> 00:07:05.280
Things are definitely looking bleak for Sam. With&nbsp;
another victim coming forward and unknowingly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:05.280 --> 00:07:08.800
corroborating Kelly’s story by repeating what&nbsp;
she said, there’s little room for doubt with&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:08.800 --> 00:07:12.640
his crime. Though it’s easy to fault Suzie for&nbsp;
not coming forward earlier, these things are&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:12.640 --> 00:07:16.960
difficult to report. It’s just easier for people&nbsp;
like Kelly, who’s already rich and powerful.

00:07:17.680 --> 00:07:21.120
Before the trial, Sandra and Baxter tell the&nbsp;
press that they're confident Sam will get what&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:21.120 --> 00:07:25.600
he deserves. However, Suzie breaks under Bowden's&nbsp;
questioning and admits to court that Sam didn't&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:25.600 --> 00:07:29.520
really defile her. She says she was just pissed&nbsp;
at him for not bailing her out of jail when she&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:29.520 --> 00:07:33.200
was arrested for narcotics possession,&nbsp;
leaving everyone in court in disbelief.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:33.200 --> 00:07:37.120
As she continues to confess, Suzie also tells&nbsp;
the court that Sam didn't sleep with Kelly,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:37.120 --> 00:07:41.280
either. Kelly’s just in love with him and wants&nbsp;
to get back at him for sleeping with Sandra.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:41.280 --> 00:07:44.480
Humiliated and enraged, Kelly gets&nbsp;
up and throws a glass at Suzie,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:44.480 --> 00:07:48.400
but she’s immediately taken away before she could&nbsp;
cause more damage. After the fiasco at court,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:48.400 --> 00:07:51.440
Bowden celebrates as he plans to&nbsp;
file a lawsuit against Sandra.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:51.440 --> 00:07:54.960
A case of jealousy and betrayal, Suzie and&nbsp;
Kelly are desperate girls who are willing to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:54.960 --> 00:07:58.960
ruin a man's life just to avenge their wounded&nbsp;
egos. The girls are lucky the judge doesn't&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:58.960 --> 00:08:03.120
punish them for committing perjury, but Bowden&nbsp;
isn't the type to let that kind of scheme slide.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:03.120 --> 00:08:06.640
It is only fair that Sam demands compensation&nbsp;
for what he went through because after all,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:06.640 --> 00:08:10.320
the money he'll get won't even be enough to pay&nbsp;
for the damages the girls have done to his life.

00:08:10.320 --> 00:08:14.240
After Bowden set up a meeting with Baxter and&nbsp;
Sandra, Sam finally gets his settlement pay,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:14.240 --> 00:08:18.400
and Bowden tells him to enjoy the money. Later&nbsp;
that day, Sam goes back to school to retrieve his&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:18.400 --> 00:08:22.640
belongings. As he is about to leave, Sam bumps&nbsp;
into Kelly, who is infuriated that Sandra is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:22.640 --> 00:08:26.720
using her trust fund to pay Sam. Kelly attacks&nbsp;
Sam in front of everyone, repeatedly hitting&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:26.720 --> 00:08:30.720
him with a book while screaming about how much&nbsp;
she hates him. Once Kelly is taken away, Sam&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:30.720 --> 00:08:34.560
tells Artie that he couldn't come back to school&nbsp;
even though he wanted to. Kelly's outburst only&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:34.560 --> 00:08:38.080
proves how bitter she is, and she doesn't even&nbsp;
hesitate to make a scene in front of everyone.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:38.080 --> 00:08:42.000
It is a pity that Sam won't be able to go back to&nbsp;
his work. This only proves that he was right when&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:42.000 --> 00:08:45.520
he said that being accused of committing carnal&nbsp;
abuse isn't something that would just go away.

00:08:45.520 --> 00:08:50.000
