but Suzie manages to break free from her. As&nbsp;
she swims towards the stairs, Kelly grabs her by&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:17.280 --> 00:11:21.760
the leg and realizes that Suzie really is scared.&nbsp;
Eventually calming down, the girls start kissing,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:21.760 --> 00:11:25.840
and as they make out, Ray continues to record&nbsp;
them. In spite of the scheming they took part in,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:25.840 --> 00:11:29.760
Kelly and Suzie are just volatile young girls.&nbsp;
Sam must have realized this, and this makes&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:29.760 --> 00:11:33.760
them easy pickings for exploitation. On one&nbsp;
hand, you have Kelly, who’s still hung up on&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:33.760 --> 00:11:37.120
her father’s death while not receiving enough&nbsp;
attention from her mother. Then there’s Suzie,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:37.120 --> 00:11:41.200
who’s clearly a troubled girl with her own string&nbsp;
of problems, financial and otherwise. Being the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:41.200 --> 00:11:44.640
guidance counsellor, you’d think that Sam would&nbsp;
do his job and actually give them guidance and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:44.640 --> 00:11:48.720
counsel, but instead, he fools around with&nbsp;
both their bodies and Kelly’s trust fund.

00:11:48.720 --> 00:11:51.120
The next day, Ray shows the&nbsp;
footage to his colleagues,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:51.120 --> 00:11:54.880
but Bryce isn't happy that Ray went to the&nbsp;
Van Ryans' property without authorization.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:54.880 --> 00:11:58.640
And unfortunately, the audio from the recording&nbsp;
is unintelligible, so they can’t hear the girls&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:58.640 --> 00:12:03.040
talking about Sam. Though Bryce warns about Sandra&nbsp;
suing for invasion of privacy, Ray is unmoved and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:03.040 --> 00:12:06.880
reveals that he brought Sam in for questioning.&nbsp;
Sam is furious, and he threatens to sue them&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:06.880 --> 00:12:11.120
next time Ray drags him to the station. When he’s&nbsp;
free to go, Sam insults Ray then takes his leave.

00:12:11.760 --> 00:12:15.200
After some time, Kelly takes a drunken&nbsp;
Suzie by the beach, where Sam is waiting&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:15.200 --> 00:12:18.880
for them. He tells Suzie that he wants them to&nbsp;
celebrate one last time before they split up,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:18.880 --> 00:12:23.120
and she agrees. However, when Sam orders&nbsp;
Kelly to get a blanket from her mom's car,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:23.120 --> 00:12:26.560
he repeatedly attacks Suzie with&nbsp;
a bottle of champagne. After that,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:26.560 --> 00:12:30.720
Sam and Kelly wrap Suzie's body in plastic before&nbsp;
loading her to the back of the Range Rover.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:30.720 --> 00:12:34.480
Sam then casually wipes the blood off his face&nbsp;
before going to the swamp to dispose of Suzie's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:34.480 --> 00:12:38.640
body. Kelly is visibly shaken after hearing&nbsp;
Suzie's screams, but it is unclear if she's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:38.640 --> 00:12:42.080
aware of Sam's plan to kill the girl right&nbsp;
from the beginning. Maybe she thought they&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:42.080 --> 00:12:46.160
were really just going to celebrate by the beach,&nbsp;
or maybe, she deliberately lured Suzie there so&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:46.160 --> 00:12:51.120
Sam could take her out of the equation. After all,&nbsp;
Suzie's death means more money for Kelly and Sam.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:51.120 --> 00:12:54.240
And since Suzie’s the weakest link, having&nbsp;
her gone would make them feel safer.

00:12:54.960 --> 00:12:58.880
Ray and Gloria then investigate Suzie’s&nbsp;
disappearance. Ray asserts that Kelly and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:58.880 --> 00:13:03.440
Sam are responsible for it then asks Gloria to&nbsp;
check on Suzie's car for him. Meanwhile, Ray&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:03.440 --> 00:13:07.440
goes to the beach with Jimmy, where the boy shows&nbsp;
him the spot where he and Suzie used to hang out.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:07.440 --> 00:13:12.000
As he investigates the place, Ray finds traces&nbsp;
of blood on an old boat and teeth in the dirt.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:15.760
Ray then calls his colleagues and the forensic&nbsp;
team to show them where Suzie was killed.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:15.760 --> 00:13:19.920
Since there's no body, Ray believes that Sam has&nbsp;
dumped Suzie in the swamp. After learning that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:19.920 --> 00:13:23.840
Suzie's car has been found at the bus terminal,&nbsp;
Ray insists that Sam is behind everything and that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:23.840 --> 00:13:28.640
Kelly will be next. However, Bryce tells Ray to&nbsp;
get off the case and warns him not to go near Sam.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:28.640 --> 00:13:33.040
But as soon as he's out of earshot, Ray asks&nbsp;
Gloria to keep an eye on Sam, and in exchange,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:33.040 --> 00:13:36.960
he will drop the investigation if the teeth&nbsp;
are not Suzie’s. Although Ray won't show it,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:36.960 --> 00:13:40.480
he must be thrilled that he'll finally be able&nbsp;
to nail Sam. Suzie doesn't mean a thing to him&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:40.480 --> 00:13:44.320
anyway, and her disappearance just gives Ray a&nbsp;
chance to go after the former guidance counselor.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:44.320 --> 00:13:48.240
Ray is so confident that Sam is the culprit&nbsp;
that he isn't even looking for other suspects.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:48.240 --> 00:13:51.920
However, Gloria doesn't feel the same way&nbsp;
and thinks her partner is mistaken about Sam.

00:13:51.920 --> 00:13:56.800
Gloria does as she's told and watches Sam, while&nbsp;
on the other hand, Sam receives a call from Kelly.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:56.800 --> 00:14:00.160
The girl is panicking, but Sam assures her that&nbsp;
they’ll be fine as long as they stick to their&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:00.160 --> 00:14:04.960
plan. He then reminds Kelly to stay at the guest&nbsp;
house, before going outside to talk to Gloria.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:04.960 --> 00:14:08.880
After informing him that Suzie’s missing,&nbsp;
she asks him where he was the previous night.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:08.880 --> 00:14:13.200
Ray smoothly evades the question then invites&nbsp;
Gloria to his room. There, he gives her Kelly’s&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:13.200 --> 00:14:17.520
file which shows her history of violence. Kelly&nbsp;
has once threatened the lives of Sandra and Suzie,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:17.520 --> 00:14:21.760
and as Sam tells Gloria more about Kelly's anger&nbsp;
issues, he implies that Kelly might be responsible&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:21.760 --> 00:14:26.080
for Suzie's disappearance. Trying to seduce&nbsp;
Gloria, Sam claims that he didn't tell them about&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:26.080 --> 00:14:30.080
it during the trial because he had principles&nbsp;
back then, but not anymore. He then tells Gloria&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:30.080 --> 00:14:34.160
to leave, and Gloria calls Ray to tell him&nbsp;
she's going home and that Sam is gone. Pissed,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:34.160 --> 00:14:37.920
Ray informs her that the blood found on the scene&nbsp;
matches Suzie's. To this, Gloria just tells him&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:37.920 --> 00:14:42.400
that if Suzie really is dead, then Bryce might&nbsp;
be on the right track about Kelly. Unfortunately,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:42.400 --> 00:14:46.080
the keen eye and sharp wit that Gloria had when&nbsp;
calling crap on Kelly’s victim statement is now&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:46.080 --> 00:14:50.560
nowhere to be found. Perhaps Suzie had it with&nbsp;
her when she was killed. To be more accurate,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:50.560 --> 00:14:54.800
though, Gloria just finds him hot. With how&nbsp;
Sandra and Sam have been finessing everyone,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:54.800 --> 00:14:58.640
it just goes to show that the strongest forces&nbsp;
in the world are big dollar bills and attractive,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:58.640 --> 00:15:03.040
scheming men. But the third strongest force&nbsp;
happens to be the ego of a detective with a hunch,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:03.040 --> 00:15:05.520
so it’s anyone’s guess as to&nbsp;
what will win out in the end.

00:15:05.520 --> 00:15:09.680
Worried about Kelly, Ray goes to the Van Ryans'&nbsp;
residence to look for her. When Ray enters the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:09.680 --> 00:15:13.600
house, he is greeted by an agitated Kelly,&nbsp;
who wants to know why he's there. The two&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:13.600 --> 00:15:17.920
then engage in a struggle, and after three shots&nbsp;
are fired, Ray comes out of the house, injured.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:17.920 --> 00:15:22.560
Seeing the officer on the ground, Sandra rushes&nbsp;
inside and screams upon finding Kelly's body.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:22.560 --> 00:15:25.840
At the station, Ray recounts how Kelly&nbsp;
attacked and shot him in the shoulder,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:25.840 --> 00:15:29.120
and he claims that he had no choice&nbsp;
but to return fire. Because of this,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:29.120 --> 00:15:32.880
Ray is eventually fired from the force for&nbsp;
insubordination. After finding Suzie's blood&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:32.880 --> 00:15:36.560
in Sandra's Range Rover, the police department&nbsp;
concludes that Suzie was murdered by Kelly.

00:15:37.280 --> 00:15:41.040
After Suzie's disappearance and Kelly's death,&nbsp;
it is later revealed that Sam and Ray have been&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:41.040 --> 00:15:45.680
working together all along. Although Sam is upset&nbsp;
that Ray killed Kelly, he agrees with his partner&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:45.680 --> 00:15:49.520
when he says that they don’t have any more loose&nbsp;
ends. Since the bank will take two more days to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:49.520 --> 00:15:53.840
complete the money transfer, Ray decides to stay.&nbsp;
When you open up a Russian matryoshka doll, you’ll&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:53.840 --> 00:15:57.600
find a smaller doll inside it, and when you open&nbsp;
that smaller doll, you’ll just find another one&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:15:57.600 --> 00:16:02.480
inside it, too. That’s what the tale of Ray and&nbsp;
Sam is. Just when the story thread is unknotted,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:02.480 --> 00:16:07.120
a new twist shows up. Later on, the two are&nbsp;
sailing when Sam suddenly attacks Ray. As Ray&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:07.120 --> 00:16:11.360
leans over the railing, Sam suddenly steers the&nbsp;
wheel, causing Ray to fall overboard. However,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:11.360 --> 00:16:15.040
Ray manages to hold on to the boat, and he&nbsp;
attacks Sam, who pretends to be clueless.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:15.040 --> 00:16:19.520
As the men fight each other, Suzie suddenly&nbsp;
appears. She’s actually alive, and she’s sporting&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:24.720
a new hairdo. With a speargun, the girl quickly&nbsp;
shoots Ray in the leg. Ray asks for Sam's help,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:24.720 --> 00:16:29.440
but Sam ignores him, saying he shouldn't have&nbsp;
killed Kelly and Suzie's friend, Davy. Suzie&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:29.440 --> 00:16:34.320
then shoots him again, and Ray goes overboard once&nbsp;
more. Suzie and Sam then watch Ray as he bleeds,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:34.320 --> 00:16:38.880
struggling to stay afloat. At this point, it would&nbsp;
just be easier to assume that the entire town is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:38.880 --> 00:16:43.120
in on Sam’s scheme. The man is a masterclass in&nbsp;
deception, and Suzie is unbelievable herself.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:43.680 --> 00:16:47.280
After all, the girl had her death faked&nbsp;
just to have a bigger share in the millions.

00:16:47.280 --> 00:16:51.920
Sometime later on, Gloria visits Ruby to talk&nbsp;
about Ray. Ruby informs her that Ray used to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:51.920 --> 00:16:55.280
have a relationship with one of the girls over&nbsp;
at the glades, and Davy had a crush on her.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:55.840 --> 00:17:01.200
One time, Davy caught Ray beating the girl, so Ray&nbsp;
killed him. Suzie, however, witnessed everything,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:01.200 --> 00:17:05.120
so Ray busted Suzie and sent her to jail&nbsp;
for six months just to prove that he could.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:05.120 --> 00:17:09.440
She then reveals to Gloria that Ray got Sandra's&nbsp;
mom pregnant with Suzie, making Sandra and Suzie&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:09.440 --> 00:17:13.680
half-sisters. When Sandra's mom died, Ruby&nbsp;
took in Suzie and raised her like her own&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:13.680 --> 00:17:18.480
granddaughter. Before Gloria leaves, she sees&nbsp;
Ruby's son, Walter, tending to Suzie's boat.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:18.480 --> 00:17:23.200
Gloria is surprised that Suzie can sail, and&nbsp;
Walter tells her that Suzie's IQ is above 200.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:23.200 --> 00:17:27.360
Another unexpected revelation is that Suzie&nbsp;
is actually Kelly's half-aunt. Gloria, who's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:27.360 --> 00:17:31.520
been partners with Ray for quite some time now,&nbsp;
clearly doesn't know that he's a dirty detective.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:31.520 --> 00:17:35.600
He's been abusing his power ever since, and&nbsp;
he's had no problems covering up his deeds.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:35.600 --> 00:17:39.120
Meanwhile, Suzie, who's been portrayed&nbsp;
as a teen with no future at all,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:39.120 --> 00:17:44.320
is actually a genius. Unfortunately, she's forced&nbsp;
to use her wits to do bad things just to survive.

00:17:44.320 --> 00:17:48.480
Back at the boat, Suzie poisons Sam and knocks&nbsp;
him overboard. It is then revealed that Suzie&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:48.480 --> 00:17:52.240
is the one who hatched the plan of getting&nbsp;
money from Sandra. Initially, she blackmailed&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:52.240 --> 00:17:56.240
Sam by showing him his pictures with Kelly in&nbsp;
bed. She's also the one who instructed Sam to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:17:56.240 --> 00:18:00.000
befriend Ray and involve him in her scheme, and&nbsp;
later on, she forced Sam to pull out two of her&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:04.640
teeth. However, Sam couldn't do it, so she did&nbsp;
it herself. It is also revealed that Ray killed&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:18:04.640 --> 00:18:08.480
Kelly and planted the gun in her hand before&nbsp;
shooting himself to make it look like a struggle.

00:18:08.480 --> 00:18:12.000
After some time, Bowden meets with Suzie and&nbsp;
gives her the money they got from Sandra.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:15.520
He informs her that he's already set aside&nbsp;
the money for Ruby and Walter, and of course,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:18:15.520 --> 00:18:19.360
his fee. As Suzie walks away with the&nbsp;
cash, Bowden reminds her to be good.

00:18:20.080 --> 00:18:23.360
Suzie must've waited long to get her scheme&nbsp;
into motion because what she did required&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:18:23.360 --> 00:18:27.280
insane patience and elaborate planning. To&nbsp;
say that Suzie is smart is an understatement,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:18:27.280 --> 00:18:30.240
for she has successfully eliminated&nbsp;
everyone in her path to get the money.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:18:30.240 --> 00:18:33.840
She is also cunning enough to cover her tracks,&nbsp;
making sure that nothing goes back to her.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:18:33.840 --> 00:18:37.520
For the final twist in this story, Bowden's&nbsp;
involvement in Suzie's plans shows that one&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:18:37.520 --> 00:18:40.080
can easily get what they want, if&nbsp;
they just know which side to take.

